data.value: Description of the Program: The program consists of five forms. The five forms are as follows: SplashScreen, Linked List, Input/Output, Mouser and About form. The SplashScreen is the startup form that includes the progress bar, and has an image to display in the background as the program loads. The Linked List is the main form which contains the following functioning buttons: Clear, Add Item, and Remove Item. The Linked List is a form that lists TSTC campuses. Input/Output form has two text files that computes the following: the total of the grades, the average grades, and the letter grade of the grades in the array. Mouser form when clicked fives the user updated coordinates and is used to click on buttons within the program. The About form contains the logo, a label containing the information of the program and a close button to return to the main screen.
